In England, in the seven days to 26 November, there were 249,468 new confirmed cases (441.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 November, there were 240,870 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (8,598 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 01 December is 8,713,738 (15,408.9 cases per 100,000 population).
